---
import AppShell from "../components/AppShell.astro";
import ScrollArrows from "../components/ScrollArrows.astro";
import type { AboutKind } from "../types";

interface Props {
  kinds: AboutKind[];
}

const { kinds } = Astro.props;
---

<AppShell activeNav="About" hideSelectedHud>
  <section class="tl-page-head is-spacious">
    <h1>About.</h1>
  </section>

  <section class="tl-about-portrait" aria-label="Portrait">
    <img
      src="/images/about-portrait.jpg"
      alt="Tom smiling in warm side light."
      width="2048"
      height="2048"
      loading="eager"
      decoding="async"
    />
  </section>

  <section class="tl-about-prose tl-prose-body">
    <p class="tl-about-lede">thinkinglabs is my public working surface.</p>

    <p>
      It is not a portfolio and not quite a blog. It is closer to a desk left in public: rough
      thoughts, stricter claims, predictions, project notes, decisions, questions, and the outside
      inputs that changed the shape of the work.
    </p>

    <p>
      I work mostly on AI systems and the operational layer around them. The parts I care about
      tend to be the parts that make systems legible: what changed, why a decision was made, what
      evidence supports a claim, and what would make me change my mind.
    </p>

    <p>
      The site is generated from a markdown repository. The repository is the durable object. The
      web UI, JSON feeds, SQLite index, and MCP surfaces are derived views over the same source.
      That constraint keeps the place quiet: edit the files, rebuild the surfaces, let the public
      version stay close to the working version.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="tl-about-structure" aria-labelledby="about-inventory-title">
    <header class="tl-about-structure-head">
      <div class="tl-eyebrow">structure</div>
      <h2 id="about-inventory-title">The public shape of the repository.</h2>
      <p>
        Each entry type has a job. Some are loose enough to catch a thought before it disappears;
        others are strict enough to make drift visible.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="tl-about-structure-rail" data-tl-about-structure-rail>
      {
        kinds.map((kind) => (
          <article class="tl-about-structure-card">
            <a
              class="tl-about-structure-link"
              href={kind.href}
              aria-label={`${kind.name}: ${kind.gloss}`}
            >
              <span
                class="tl-about-structure-visual"
                data-entity={kind.slug}
                aria-hidden="true"
              />
              <span class="tl-about-structure-meta">
                <span class="tl-about-structure-kicker">
                  {kind.count} {kind.count === 1 ? "entry" : "entries"}
                </span>
                <span class="tl-about-structure-title">{kind.name}</span>
                <span class="tl-about-structure-gloss">{kind.gloss}</span>
              </span>
            </a>
          </article>
        ))
      }
    </div>
    <ScrollArrows
      target="[data-tl-about-structure-rail]"
      items=".tl-about-structure-card"
      label="Structure cards"
      rowOnly
    />
  </section>

  <section class="tl-about-prose tl-prose-body">
    <div class="tl-eyebrow">how to read it</div>
    <p>
      The pages here are allowed to be incomplete. A claim can be revised. A prediction can resolve
      badly. A project can go dormant. The useful thing is not that every object is polished, but
      that the system leaves enough structure behind to return later and inspect what happened.
    </p>
    <p>
      I want the tone of the site to stay calm because the work benefits from calm. There should be
      enough empty space to read a sentence, enough metadata to audit it, and not much more than
      that.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="tl-about-prose tl-prose-body">
    <div class="tl-eyebrow">work</div>
    <p>
      I work for <a href="https://wild.as">https://wild.as</a>, by the way. Reach out to me there at
      <a href="mailto:tom@wild.as">tom@wild.as</a> or
      <a href="mailto:tom@flaming.codes">tom@flaming.codes</a> for personal messages.
      I also own <a href="https://flaming.codes">https://flaming.codes</a>, my previous site, which
      is still live and follows a more traditional blogging format.
    </p>
    <p>
      Wild works with the latest technologies in the pragmatic sense: not chasing novelty for its
      own sake, but putting new capabilities into production when they make software clearer,
      faster, or more useful. A large part of that work right now is agentic software engineering:
      using agents every day, building the harnesses around them, and learning where human judgment
      still has to stay close to the loop.
    </p>
    <p>
      That is also why this site looks the way it does. The repository, the metadata, the MCP
      surfaces, and the review flows are not separate from the work. They are part of the same
      attempt to make AI-assisted engineering inspectable, repeatable, and worth trusting.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="tl-about-colophon" aria-label="Colophon">
    <div>
      <div class="tl-eyebrow">colophon</div>
      <p>
        Built with Astro, markdown content collections, deterministic feeds, a derived SQLite
        index, and a small MCP server for agent access. The typography and navigation are meant to
        make the repository feel like a working surface rather than a publication schedule.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</AppShell>

<style>
  .tl-about-portrait,
  .tl-about-prose,
  .tl-about-colophon {
    width: var(--tl-center);
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  .tl-about-portrait {
    margin-top: -8vh;
    margin-bottom: clamp(4.5rem, 12vh, 8rem);
  }

  .tl-about-portrait img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }

  .tl-about-prose {
    padding-bottom: clamp(4rem, 12vh, 8rem);
  }

  .tl-about-lede {
    max-width: 16ch;
    color: var(--tl-ink);
    font-size: clamp(32px, 4.8vw, 58px);
    font-weight: 620;
    line-height: 0.98;
    letter-spacing: -0.045em;
  }

  .tl-about-prose .tl-eyebrow {
    margin-bottom: 1.35rem;
  }

  .tl-about-structure {
    position: relative;
    width: 100%;
    padding: clamp(4rem, 12vh, 8rem) 0;
  }

  .tl-about-structure-head {
    width: var(--tl-center);
    margin: 0 auto clamp(2.75rem, 7vh, 4.5rem);
  }

  .tl-about-structure-head h2 {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    max-width: 12ch;
    font-size: clamp(30px, 4vw, 50px);
    font-weight: 620;
    line-height: 0.98;
    letter-spacing: -0.045em;
  }

  .tl-about-structure-head p {
    max-width: 36rem;
    margin-top: 1.2rem;
    color: var(--tl-muted);
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .tl-about-structure-rail {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 6rem);
    width: 100%;
    padding-block: clamp(2rem, 5vh, 4rem);
    overflow-x: auto;
    overflow-y: visible;
    overscroll-behavior-x: contain;
    scrollbar-width: none;
    scroll-snap-type: x mandatory;
    -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;
  }

  .tl-about-structure-rail::-webkit-scrollbar {
    width: 0;
    height: 0;
  }

  .tl-about-structure-card {
    position: relative;
    flex: 0 0 auto;
    width: clamp(var(--card-width, 16rem), 18vw, calc(var(--card-width, 16rem) + 6rem));
    --card-width: 16rem;
    --card-half: clamp(8rem, 9vw, 12.5rem);
    --card-aspect: 1 / 1;
    --tl-card-shadow: var(--tl-gallery-shadow);
    --tl-card-hover-shadow:
      0 2px 3px rgba(7, 9, 13, 0.03),
      0 16px 34px -18px rgba(7, 9, 13, 0.22),
      0 40px 82px -42px rgba(7, 9, 13, 0.22),
      0 96px 154px -82px rgba(7, 9, 13, 0.18);
    scroll-snap-align: center;
  }

  .tl-about-structure-card:nth-child(7n+1) { --card-width: 16rem;   --card-half: clamp(8rem, 9vw, 12.5rem);    --card-aspect: 3 / 4; }
  .tl-about-structure-card:nth-child(7n+2) { --card-width: 22rem;   --card-half: clamp(11rem, 9vw, 15.5rem);   --card-aspect: 4 / 3; }
  .tl-about-structure-card:nth-child(7n+3) { --card-width: 16rem;   --card-half: clamp(8rem, 9vw, 12.5rem);    --card-aspect: 3 / 4; }
  .tl-about-structure-card:nth-child(7n+4) { --card-width: 17.5rem; --card-half: clamp(8.75rem, 9vw, 13.25rem); --card-aspect: 1 / 1; }
  .tl-about-structure-card:nth-child(7n+5) { --card-width: 22rem;   --card-half: clamp(11rem, 9vw, 15.5rem);   --card-aspect: 4 / 3; }
  .tl-about-structure-card:nth-child(7n+6) { --card-width: 16rem;   --card-half: clamp(8rem, 9vw, 12.5rem);    --card-aspect: 3 / 4; }
  .tl-about-structure-card:nth-child(7n+7) { --card-width: 17.5rem; --card-half: clamp(8.75rem, 9vw, 13.25rem); --card-aspect: 1 / 1; }

  .tl-about-structure-card:first-child {
    margin-inline-start: calc(50vw - var(--card-half, 8rem));
  }

  .tl-about-structure-card:last-child {
    margin-inline-end: calc(50vw - var(--card-half, 8rem));
  }

  .tl-about-structure-link {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.1rem;
    color: inherit;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .tl-about-structure-link:focus-visible {
    outline: none;
  }

  .tl-about-structure-link:focus-visible .tl-about-structure-visual {
    outline: 2px solid #2f6bff;
    outline-offset: 4px;
  }

  .tl-about-structure-visual {
    position: relative;
    display: block;
    overflow: hidden;
    aspect-ratio: var(--card-aspect, 1 / 1);
    background: var(--tl-entity-gradient, var(--tl-soft));
    box-shadow: var(--tl-card-shadow);
    transition: box-shadow 0.55s ease;
  }

  .tl-about-structure-visual::before {
    position: absolute;
    inset: -18%;
    background: var(--tl-entity-gradient, var(--tl-soft));
    content: "";
    transform: rotate(0deg) scale(1.2);
    transform-origin: var(--tl-gradient-origin, 50% 50%);
    animation: tl-entity-tile-drift var(--tl-gradient-duration, 26s) ease-in-out infinite alternate;
  }

  .tl-about-structure-link:hover .tl-about-structure-visual,
  .tl-about-structure-link:focus-visible .tl-about-structure-visual {
    box-shadow: var(--tl-card-hover-shadow);
  }

  .tl-about-structure-meta {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.42rem;
    padding: 0 0.1rem;
  }

  .tl-about-structure-kicker {
    color: rgba(12, 20, 36, 0.56);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 540;
    line-height: 1;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .tl-about-structure-title {
    color: var(--tl-ink);
    font-size: clamp(18px, 1.8vw, 22px);
    font-weight: 650;
    line-height: 1.08;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .tl-about-structure-gloss {
    color: rgba(12, 20, 36, 0.66);
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 420;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .tl-about-structure :global(.tl-scroll-arrows) {
    position: static;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    margin: 1.75rem auto 0;
    transform: none;
  }

  .tl-about-colophon {
    padding: clamp(4rem, 12vh, 8rem) 0 18vh;
  }

  .tl-about-colophon p {
    margin-top: 1.35rem;
    max-width: 38rem;
    color: rgba(7, 9, 13, 0.68);
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  @media (max-width: 767px) {
    .tl-about-portrait,
    .tl-about-prose,
    .tl-about-colophon {
      width: min(100% - 40px, 43.75rem);
    }

    .tl-about-structure-head {
      width: min(100% - 40px, 43.75rem);
    }

    .tl-about-portrait {
      margin-top: -4vh;
    }

    .tl-about-structure-rail {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 3rem;
      padding-block: 1.5rem;
      padding-inline: 20px;
      overflow: visible;
      scroll-snap-type: none;
    }

    .tl-about-structure-card {
      width: min(100%, var(--card-width-mobile, 13.5rem));
    }

    .tl-about-structure-card:nth-child(3n+2) {
      --card-width-mobile: 18rem;
    }

    .tl-about-structure-card:first-child,
    .tl-about-structure-card:last-child {
      margin-inline: 0;
    }
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .tl-about-structure-visual::before {
      animation: none;
    }
  }
</style>
